            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# ---- Antenna beamwidths from physical dimensions ----\ntheta_az = lam / La           # azimuth (along-track) beamwidth [rad]\ntheta_rg = lam / Lr           # range (elevation) beamwidth [rad]\n\ndef antenna_pattern(squint):\n    return np.sinc(squint / theta_az) ** 2\n\ndef antenna_pattern_2d(az_ang, rg_ang):\n    return np.sinc(az_ang / theta_az) ** 2 * np.sinc(rg_ang / theta_rg) ** 2\n\nprint('antenna: theta_az=%.4f deg, theta_rg=%.4f deg' % (np.rad2deg(theta_az), np.rad2deg(theta_rg)))\n\n# ---- 2-D radiation pattern as a 3D surface (binary single-renderer path) ----\n# equal angular span on both axes so the narrow azimuth beam vs the wider\n# range beam is read honestly.\nang_max = 3 * max(theta_az, theta_rg)\n_az = np.linspace(-ang_max, ang_max, 240)\n_rg = np.linspace(-ang_max, ang_max, 240)\nAZ, RG = np.meshgrid(_az, _rg)\nG = antenna_pattern_2d(AZ, RG)              # linear power 0..1\n# surface3d_gl takes 20*log10(|field|); pass sqrt(G) so dB = 10*log10(G) (power dB)\nsurface3d_gl(np.sqrt(G), np.rad2deg(_az), np.rad2deg(_rg),\n          'Antenna 2-D radiation pattern',\n          xlabel='azimuth angle [deg]', ylabel='range angle [deg]')",
            "label": "Antenna",
            "spec": "REAL HW: antenna pattern shapes the illumination. Characteristics (mindmap): range direction, azimuth direction, gain.\n\nSimulation: azimuth pattern modeled as normalized-sinc^2 with first null at the beamwidth theta_a:\n  pat(squint) = sinc(squint/theta_a)^2\nThis is a first-null beamwidth approximation (NOT 3 dB). Range-direction pattern and absolute gain are not modeled (relative pattern only)."
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true,
          "executionOrder": 13
        },
        "width": 400,
        "style": {}
      },
