      {
        "id": "n25",
        "type": "canvasNode",
        "position": {
          "x": -488.98322183952496,
          "y": 1927
        },
        "data": {
          "label": "Python Code",
          "category": "processing",
          "blockType": "python_code",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "in_0",
              "label": "in_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "outputs": [
            {
              "id": "out_0",
              "label": "out_0",
              "portType": "any"
            }
          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === LNA (Level 2 RF Front-End) — Explicit two-way link budget ===\n#\n# Three stages performed here, in order:\n#   1) Tx EIRP + propagation loss + Rx antenna gain  (constant for geometry)\n#   2) LNA / front-end gain                          (adjustable, level-tune knob)\n#   3) Receiver thermal noise (kTBF, Friis-dominant stage)\n#\n# === Link-budget breakdown (per pulse, X-band SAR, σ=1 m² reference) ===\n#\n#   Transmit side:\n#     P_t        = +63 dBm    Tx peak power (≈ 2 kW, X-band satellite SAR class)\n#     G_t        = 10·log10(4π·η·La·Lr / λ²)   computed from antenna aperture\n#                              (η = 0.6 efficiency, La/Lr from n1, λ from n6)\n#     ---------\n#     EIRP       = P_t + G_t\n#\n#   Two-way free-space path loss for σ_ref = 1 m² point scatterer at R0:\n#     L_path     = 30·log10(4π) + 40·log10(R0) - 20·log10(λ) - 10·log10(σ_ref)\n#                = 30·log10(4π) + 40·log10(R0) - 20·log10(λ)         [σ_ref = 1]\n#     (Per-scatterer 1/R² variation around R0 is already applied in n32.)\n#\n#   Receive side:\n#     G_r        = same antenna formula as G_t (monostatic, shared aperture)\n#     G_LNA      = adjustable LNA / total Rx-chain gain  [slider n53: g_lna_db]\n#\n#   Net voltage scaling applied to normalized s_raw:\n#     K_total    = 10 ** ((EIRP - L_path + G_r + G_LNA) / 20)\n#\n# === Why G_LNA is large (~100..150 dB) in this simulator ===\n#\n# n32 outputs s_raw in a normalized form where the reference scatterer produces\n# |s_raw| ≈ 1.0. A *physical* receiver at ~600 km, σ=1 m² sees ~-156 dBm at the\n# antenna; reaching ADC FS = 1 V into 50 Ω (+10 dBm peak) requires ~+165 dB of\n# receiver-chain voltage gain. A real system distributes this across LNA\n# (+30..50 dB), mixer/IF, baseband amp and AGC. This simulator lumps it into\n# one G_LNA knob; the breakdown above accounts for each physical stage.\n#\n# Tune G_LNA so the calibration reference (1 point target at σ°=0 dB, centre)\n# lands a few dB below 0 dBFS (default ~ -30 dBFS) for headroom. Brighter\n# scenes will land higher and may clip the ADC — that is realistic SAR\n# behaviour. Thermal noise floor is held at a fixed ADC-referred level (kTBF\n# at the receiver input, mapped directly to ADC units) so that adjusting\n# G_LNA moves the signal, not the noise — i.e. SNR genuinely changes with\n# the knob (vs. AGC which keeps signal pinned).\n#\n# === Connection to other nodes ===\n#   nf_db     ← gui_slider n26 (Noise Figure)\n#   g_lna_db  ← gui_slider n53 (LNA / total Rx-chain gain, level-tune knob)\n#   R0, lam   ← n6  (geometry)\n#   La, Lr, B ← n1  (Common Parameters)\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport time as _time\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\n# --- Physical constants ---\nk_boltz  = 1.380649e-23   # Boltzmann constant [J/K]\nT_K      = 290.0          # System noise temperature [K]\nR_load   = 50.0           # Receiver input impedance [Ω]\nADC_FS_V = 1.0            # ADC full-scale = ±1.0 V (= +10 dBm peak @ 50 Ω)\n\n# --- Hard-coded link-budget design values ---\nP_t_dbm      = 63.0       # Tx peak power [dBm]      (≈ 2 kW)\neta_ant      = 0.6        # Antenna aperture efficiency (typical X-band)\nsigma_ref_m2 = 1.0        # Reference RCS for path-loss term [m²]\n\n# --- Slider parameters ---\nnf_db = float(globals().get('nf_db', 3.0))   # Noise figure [dB]\n\n# --- Link-budget breakdown (computed from geometry / antenna params) ---\nG_ant_dbi  = 10.0 * np.log10(4.0 * np.pi * eta_ant * La * Lr / (lam ** 2))   # G_t = G_r\nEIRP_dbm   = P_t_dbm + G_ant_dbi\nL_path_db  = (30.0 * np.log10(4.0 * np.pi)\n              + 40.0 * np.log10(R0)\n              - 20.0 * np.log10(lam)\n              - 10.0 * np.log10(sigma_ref_m2))\nchain_db_no_lna = EIRP_dbm - L_path_db + G_ant_dbi   # EIRP − L_path + G_r (constant)\n\n# --- Resolve G_LNA from slider (g_lna_db preferred; legacy signal_peak_dbfs is\n#     interpreted as a calibration *target* dBFS for the reference scatterer\n#     and converted to the equivalent G_LNA so old workspaces stay consistent).\nif 'g_lna_db' in globals():\n    g_lna_db = float(globals()['g_lna_db'])\nelif 'signal_peak_dbfs' in globals():\n    _legacy_target = float(globals()['signal_peak_dbfs'])\n    g_lna_db = _legacy_target - chain_db_no_lna\n    print('  (legacy slider) signal_peak_dbfs=%+.1f dBFS  →  g_lna_db=%+.1f dB'\n          % (_legacy_target, g_lna_db))\nelse:\n    g_lna_db = -chain_db_no_lna - 30.0   # sensible default: reference at -30 dBFS\n\nnet_db  = chain_db_no_lna + g_lna_db\nK_total = 10.0 ** (net_db / 20.0)\n\n# --- Step 1: apply full link-budget chain to s_raw ---\ncurrent_peak_before = float(np.abs(s_raw).max())\ns_raw = (s_raw * K_total).astype(np.complex64)\ncurrent_peak_after = float(np.abs(s_raw).max())\n\n# --- Step 2: thermal noise (kTBF, dropped at the ADC, not amplified through G_rx) ---\n# Design choice: noise floor is held at a fixed ADC-referred dBFS so that\n# G_LNA only moves the signal. This gives the user a clean \"SNR vs gain\"\n# relationship for testing ADC clipping vs. noise-floor crossover.\nF_lin             = 10.0 ** (nf_db / 10.0)\nthermal_power_W   = k_boltz * T_K * B * F_lin\nthermal_voltage_V = float(np.sqrt(thermal_power_W * R_load))\nnoise_std         = thermal_voltage_V / ADC_FS_V\nnoise_floor_dbfs  = 20.0 * np.log10(noise_std + 1e-30)\n\nNOISE_SEED = 1\nrng = np.random.RandomState(int(NOISE_SEED) & 0xFFFFFFFF)\nnoise = (noise_std / np.sqrt(2.0)) * (\n    rng.standard_normal(s_raw.shape) + 1j * rng.standard_normal(s_raw.shape)\n)\ns_raw = (s_raw + noise).astype(np.complex64)\n\n# --- Diagnostics ---\nachieved_peak_dbfs = 20.0 * np.log10(current_peak_after / ADC_FS_V + 1e-30)\nclip_pct = 100.0 * float(np.mean((np.abs(s_raw.real) > ADC_FS_V) | (np.abs(s_raw.imag) > ADC_FS_V)))\nsnr_db = achieved_peak_dbfs - noise_floor_dbfs\n\nprint('LNA Level 2 (explicit link budget): NF=%.1f dB  B=%.1f MHz  T=%.0f K'\n      % (nf_db, B/1e6, T_K))\nprint('  Two-way SAR link budget (σ_ref=%.0f m², R0=%.1f km, λ=%.2f cm):'\n      % (sigma_ref_m2, R0/1e3, lam*100))\nprint('    Tx side:  P_t %+.1f dBm + G_t %+.1f dBi   = EIRP  %+.1f dBm'\n      % (P_t_dbm, G_ant_dbi, EIRP_dbm))\nprint('    Channel:  path loss                     = %+.1f dB' % (-L_path_db))\nprint('    Rx side:  G_r %+.1f dBi + G_LNA %+.1f dB  (Rx total = %+.1f dB)'\n      % (G_ant_dbi, g_lna_db, G_ant_dbi + g_lna_db))\nprint('    --------')\nprint('    Net s_raw scaling:                      = %+.2f dB   (K_total = %.3e)'\n      % (net_db, K_total))\nprint('  Scene s_raw peak:  %.3g (norm)  →  %.3g V   (%+.1f dBFS)'\n      % (current_peak_before, current_peak_after, achieved_peak_dbfs))\nif clip_pct > 0:\n    print('  ⚠️ ADC clipping: %.2f%% of samples > FS — lower G_LNA or σ°_max for headroom'\n          % clip_pct)\nprint('  Thermal noise floor (ADC-referred): %+.1f dBFS   (σ=%.3g V at FS=%.1f V)'\n      % (noise_floor_dbfs, noise_std, ADC_FS_V))\nprint('  Peak SNR (scene):                   %.1f dB     (%.2fs)'\n      % (snr_db, _time.monotonic() - _t0))\n",
            "label": "LNA (Level 2, link budget)",
            "spec": "【LNA (Level 2 RF Front-End, explicit link budget)】\n\n3段処理:\n1. リンクバジェット連鎖 (EIRP − L_path + G_r + G_LNA) を s_raw に voltage scaling として一括適用。アンテナ寸法 (La, Lr) と波長 (λ) から G_t = G_r を 4π·η·La·Lr/λ² で算出。調整ノブは G_LNA (slider n53) 一個に集約。\n2. 熱雑音 (kTBF) — ADC基準で固定。G_LNA を変えても雑音床は動かない設計 (signal だけ動く → SNR が実際に変わる)。AGC とは別物。\n3. ADC clip 率を per-sample で表示 (>0% で飽和警告)。\n\n内訳 (コメント・出力に同じ数値を表示):\n  Tx     P_t = +63 dBm (~2 kW)\n         G_t = 10·log10(4π·η·La·Lr / λ²)   η=0.6\n         EIRP = P_t + G_t\n  Channel L_path = 30·log10(4π) + 40·log10(R0) − 20·log10(λ) − 10·log10(σ_ref=1m²)\n         (per-scatterer 1/R² 変動は n32 で既に反映済)\n  Rx     G_r = G_t (monostatic, shared aperture)\n         G_LNA = slider n53 (level-tune knob)\n  Net    K_total = 10^((EIRP − L_path + G_r + G_LNA) / 20)\n\nG_LNA が物理的に大きい (~100–150 dB) 理由:\nn32 の s_raw は |peak| ≈ 1.0 の正規化値。実物理では ~−156 dBm 相当を 1 V ADC FS に持ち上げるために ~165 dB の受信機鎖ゲインが必要。本シミュレータは LNA / mixer / IF amp / baseband / AGC を G_LNA 一つに集約している (コメントで各物理寄与は明示)。\n\n入力 (kernel namespace):\n  s_raw  ← n42/n43/n47 のいずれか (n32 で σ°_max + 1/R² 反映済)\n  R0, lam ← n6, La, Lr, B ← n1\n\nGUI 入力:\n  nf_db     ← n26 (Noise Figure dB)\n  g_lna_db  ← n53 (LNA / total Rx-chain gain, level-tune knob; default 110 dB → reference peak ≈ −30 dBFS)\n\n旧 signal_peak_dbfs スライダ (校正ターゲット dBFS) は同等の g_lna_db に内部で変換する fallback 付き。\n\n出力 (kernel namespace):\n  s_raw → 後段 SAR 処理 (n9〜n18) が消費。peak はシーン依存、ADC FS=1.0 V_peak 単位。\n  console に link budget breakdown + achieved peak dBFS + ADC clip% + noise floor + SNR を表示。\n\nシーン別の振る舞い:\n  - 点標的 1 個 (σ°=0 dB): achieved peak ≈ (chain_no_lna + g_lna_db) dBFS  (default: −30)\n  - σ°_max を +20 dB: peak が +20 dB → 飽和の可能性\n  - σ°_max を −40 dB: peak が雑音床近くまで沈む → SNR 低下を観測可能\n  - 多数散乱体の画像: コヒーレント和で peak が ~sqrt(N) 以上に成長 → ADC 飽和の可能性"
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true,
          "executionOrder": 17
        },
        "width": 400,
        "style": {}
      },
      {
